The paper discusses machine learning with tensor networks for image classification, which is a topic that falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on supervised learning and proposes new tensor-based approaches for classification. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper specifically applies the proposed methods to image datasets. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses using tensor networks for machine learning, which is a subfield of AI. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper compares the proposed methods to neural network-based classifiers. The fifth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses the use of tensor-train format for alternating ridge regression.
